state.unicode: Change the frequency of advice and how you receive it by using the two drop-down menus and the text and audio options below.

uientry.unicode: Tick this checkbox to enable the Aide de camp||When ticked, the advisor will inform you about important developements on the battlefield, such as the death of a general.

state.unicode: If this is checked you will be able to see any visible CPU player's moves during the end turn phase.||This can help to keep a track on some of the CPU's locations and movements, but the end turn phase will also take longer.

uientry.unicode: Realism mode||If this is checked, you will have to fight battles without the radar map or contextual tooltips. You will also be unable to issue orders when paused.||Your camera is also restricted to within 200 meters of any unit, and any enemy units more than 600 meters away will be hidden from sight.
Adds the 'Scare (everyone)' trait to all units in the single player campaign and custom battles, enables spooky battlefields and harpies!

state.unicode: A battle with a set time limit will end when the time is up.||If this happens, the defending army will win the battle.||With no time limit set, the battle will simply play out until one army is victorious.
